sequenceDiagram
    title Chapter 14: Thread Spawn and Join
    
    participant main as Main Thread
    participant t1 as Thread 1
    participant t2 as Thread 2
    participant handle1 as JoinHandle1
    participant handle2 as JoinHandle2
    
    main->>main: let v = vec![1, 2, 3]
    
    Note over main,t1: Spawning threads
    
    main->>t1: thread::spawn(|| { ... })
    activate t1
    t1->>t1: Execute closure
    t1->>handle1: JoinHandle returned
    handle1-->>main: handle1
    
    main->>t2: thread::spawn(|| { ... })
    activate t2
    t2->>t2: Execute closure
    t2->>handle2: JoinHandle returned
    handle2-->>main: handle2
    
    Note over main,t1: Both threads running concurrently
    
    main->>t1: handle1.join()
    t1->>t1: Continue execution
    t1->>t1: Complete work
    t1-->>main: Result<()>
    deactivate t1
    
    Note over main,t2: Thread 1 joined, Thread 2 still running
    
    main->>t2: handle2.join()
    t2->>t2: Continue execution
    t2->>t2: Complete work
    t2-->>main: Result<()>
    deactivate t2
    
    Note over main,t1: Both threads completed
    
    main->>main: Continue after both threads
    
    Note over main,t1: move keyword transfers ownership to thread
